html2wiki-desc: Import HTML content into your wiki
html2wiki-summary: Description appearing on top of [[Special:Html2Wiki]] - but it's not.
html2wiki-i18n-welcome: Welcome to the localization file of the Html2Wiki extension.
html2wiki-intro: Use this form to import HTML content into your wiki. If you upload a zip file, the Collection name field is used to differentiate the collection from a later version. Also all files will be grouped in a category by the same name. For example, if you're importing a VIP Info Hubs collection (ie. 'docs' is the root folder), you would enter a unique Collection ID like 'VIP-1.1' so that the whole collection is imported into an article hierarchy starting with 'VIP-1.1'. This way 10 different collections can be imported without clobbering each other. Specifying an existing Collection name or parent path will update existing wiki content. If you are importing a single file which should exist within an existing article hierarchy, you should specify it's 'parent' as the collection name. For example, if importing a new 'advanced_topics07.html' that should exist at 'VIP-1.1/docs/htmldocs/questa_vip_user/advanced_topics07.html', the parent would be 'VIP-1.1/docs/htmldocs/questa_vip_user/'
html2wiki-text: HTML and zip files are supported.  Images will be handled automatically from zip files.
html2wiki-not-allowed: Sorry, you must be an Admin, or have import privileges to use this form.
